        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Frame_1984078502.png",
        "content": "<p>Top-brand smartwatches can easily climb into the $800 range once you start adding features, finishes, and logos. The problem is, most of what you’re paying for has nothing to do with how he actually uses the watch.<br/><br/>At the end of the day, he cares about the basics: seeing who’s calling, reading texts, getting notifications, tracking his heart rate, sleep, and daily activity. <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>A rugged watch like our</strong></span>s does all of that without asking you to drop eight hundred bucks on something that might not survive his work week.<br/><br/>You still get the “smart” part of a smartwatch—connection, health tracking, and everyday convenience—but in a package built for real work, at a price that doesn’t make you nervous every time he bangs it on a lift or a workbench. <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>The Carbinox Blaze</strong></span> feels like a premium gift without you paying premium-brand money.</p>",
